local PC or workstation There are clients for the following The directory following the name is the location of the client on the anonymous ftp site in the directory pub Unix Curses Emacs pub gopher Unix Xwindows athena pub gopher Unix Xwindows Motif pub gopher Unix moog Xwindows Xview pub gopher Unix xvgopher Macintosh Hypercard pub gopher Macintosh TurboGopher old versions Macintosh Application pub gopher Macintosh TurboGopher DOS w Clarkson Driver pub gopher PC client NeXTstep pub gopher NeXT VM CMS pub gopher Rice CMS or pub gopher VieGOPHER VMS pub gopher VMS OS pub gopher MVS XA pub gopher mvs Many other clients and servers have been developed by others the following is an attempt at a comprehensive A Microsoft Windows Winsock client The Gopher Book pub micro pc stuff ms windows winsock goph A Macintosh Application MacGopher pub gopher Macintosh Another Macintosh application GopherApp util gopher gopherapp A port of the UNIX curses client for DOS with PC TCP public dos misc A port of the UNIX curses client for PC NFS nfs A beta version of the PC Gopher client for Novell's LAN Workplace for DOS dos gopher A VMS DECwindows client for use with Wollongong or UCX XGOPHER Note these Macintosh clients require Most of the above clients can also be fetched via a gopher client Put the following on a gopher server Type Host Port Path Name Gopher Software Or point your gopher client at port and look in the gopher There are also a number of public telnet login sites The University of Minnesota operates one on the machine See for more information about It is recommended that you run the client software instead of logging into the public telnet login A client uses the custom features of the local machine mouse scroll bars A local client is also Where are there publicly available logins ie places to telnet to in order to get a taste of gopher for Gopher Here is a short list use the site closest to you to minimize network Telnet Public Logins Hostname IP Login Area gopher Nort